<br>
I found a nice place for the low to mid 40s solo blademaster. Go to Necht and head northwest out of town. You'll go over one hill that has treants and vigilant ones on it. Keep going and go over another hill. Be careful on this one because the hill top has stillers (big floating octopus things) that are yellow/orange to a 45. Once you get over that hill, you'll be in a huge valley filled with the tree shaped guys like corrupted sylvans and treestrippers. They'll be yellow to blue con. They do crush damage so they get a minus to reinforced armor. I know blades and fire procs (my weapons of choice) get a bonus to them. Only the sylvans cast anything which is a 4 tick weak DoT. I can chew through these guys with pretty much only endurance downtime. At 45 I'm getting anywhere from 6-16 mil per kill. Doesn't sound like a bunch but I can kill a bunch quickly and it all adds up. They drop from 10-50 silver, some stackable sell loot, and the occastional unique drop. The creatures are all aggressive and move around so keep an eye out. However, the valley is huge which makes them all pretty spread out. I can usually kill one and sit down right there to regen end without fear. I rarely see anyone around so the camp bonuses stay big as long as I keep moving around the valley. <br>
<br>
Anyone find any other interesting hunting grounds?<br>
<br>
