<br>
If you keep going north past these guys, you'll come across some chalicos (big non-aggressive cow-looking things). They're orange/red to me so I don't mess with them (yet). Keep going and you'll eventually find corruptors (big evil treant things). They're yellow/orange to a 47. They're vulnerable to slash and their attacks are resistant to reinforced armor. Only thing you have to watch out for is they have a pretty mean DoT (60-80 per tick). I can usually solo them with 1/4 to 1/2 my health left, depending on parries/evades and crit hits. I bet if I find a nice bard to pair with, I can chew them up in no time.<br>
<br>
A great place for group exp is the Fomor dungeon. Fomor is set up like 3 concentric circles. Get a nice balanced group (druid, bard, warden, 2 nukers, 2 tanks, 1 whatever) and get in there. Once you enter, head to your right and follow the circle around. Pass Krackenstein (miniboss for the outer circle) and you find a place with a fighting pit in the ground. Every so often, a couple fomors will get in a pit and fight each other. This area will give you nonstop pulls of 3-4 fomors red/purp to a 47. Some good cash too and an occasional unique drop.<br>
